response: "{ \"title\": \"Euler's Totient Function\", \"description\": \"Write a function `totient(n)` that calculates Euler's totient function \\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef totient(n: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): A positive integer.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the number of positive integers less than or equal to `n` that are relatively prime to `n`.\\n\", \"code\": \"\\nimport math\\n\\ndef totient(n: int) -> int:\\n    result = 0\\n    for i in range(1, n + 1):\\n        if math.gcd(i, n) == 1:\\n            result += 1\\n    return result\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert totient(5) == 4\", \"assert totient(20) == 8\", \"assert totient(30) == 8\"] }"
